the Hornets’ 46 games…37 of those starts came at second base and three came at shortstop…started each of the final 25 games of the season, including all 19 games against a Big Sky opponent…the Hornets player…hit .207 (23-for-111) with nine runs, four doubles, seven RBIs and a team-high tying 12 sacrifices…had a pair of four-game hitting streaks…drew a two-out, walkoff walk in the Hornets’ 1-0 High School A 2010 graduate of Banning High School in Wilmington, Calif…played four years of varsity softball for the Pilots at both shortstop and third base…a four-time all-Marine League selection (second team each of her first three seasons, first team as a senior)…helped the Pilots to a combined 80-44 record during her four seasons…named the Invitational Division Player of the Year after her senior season by the Los Angeles Wave.
